==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Animalculism
<hw>An`i*mal"cu*lism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>animalculisme</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The
theory which seeks to explain certain physiological and pathological
phenomena by means of animalcules.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The theory that the
spermatozo⟦oum⟧n and not the ovum contains the whole of the embryo;
spermatism; -- opposed to <contr>ovism</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Animalculist</ent>⟦br⟧
